HEADWORD: Unconfound
<hw>Un`con*found"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>confound</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from a state
of confusion, or of being confounded.</def>
